WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.559 --> 00:00:16.314
I grew up white. secular and middle class
[AI] 我是白人。世俗和中产阶级

2
00:00:16.338 --> 00:00:18.010
in 1950s America.
[AI] 20世纪50年代的美国。

3
00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:21.740
That meant watching fireworks on the Fourth of July.
[AI] 这意味着在7月4日观看焰火表演。

4
00:00:22.683 --> 00:00:24.368
trick-or-treating on Halloween
[AI] 万圣节不给糖就捣蛋

5
00:00:24.392 --> 00:00:26.619
and putting presents under a tree at Christmas.
[AI] 圣诞节时把礼物放在树下。

6
00:00:27.158 --> 00:00:29.798
But by the time those traditions got to me.
[AI] 但是当这些传统影响到我的时候。

7
00:00:29.822 --> 00:00:32.023
they were hollow. commercial enterprises.
[AI] 它们是空心的。商业企业。

8
00:00:32.047 --> 00:00:33.939
which just left me feeling empty.
[AI] 这让我感到空虚。

9
00:00:34.810 --> 00:00:36.720
So from a relatively young age.
[AI] 所以从一个相对年轻的年龄。

10
00:00:36.744 --> 00:00:39.573
I found myself looking to fill an existential hole.
[AI] 我发现自己在寻找填补一个存在的漏洞。

11
00:00:40.227 --> 00:00:42.694
to connect with something bigger than myself.
[AI] 和比我更重要的人联系。

12
00:00:44.081 --> 00:00:47.135
There hadn't been a bar mitzvah in my family in over a century.
[AI] 我们家已经一个多世纪没有成人礼了。

13
00:00:47.159 --> 00:00:49.110
so I thought I'd take a shot at that --
[AI] 所以我想我应该试一试--

14
00:00:49.134 --> 00:00:50.448
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

15
00:00:50.472 --> 00:00:53.879
only to be devastated when my one encounter with the rabbi.
[AI] 只有在我和拉比的一次邂逅中被摧毁。

16
00:00:53.903 --> 00:00:58.650
a really tall. godlike figure with flowing white hair.
[AI] a真的很高。神性的身材，飘逸的白发。

17
00:00:58.674 --> 00:01:01.551
consisted of him asking me for my middle name
[AI] 包括他问我的中间名

18
00:01:01.575 --> 00:01:03.246
so we could fill out a form.
[AI] 所以我们可以填一张表格。

19
00:01:03.914 --> 00:01:05.234
Yep. that was it.
[AI] 是的。就这样。

20
00:01:05.258 --> 00:01:06.321
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

21
00:01:06.345 --> 00:01:08.159
So I got the fountain pen.
[AI] 所以我拿到了自来水笔。

22
00:01:08.183 --> 00:01:11.035
but I didn't get the sense of belonging and confidence
[AI] 但我没有得到归属感和信心

23
00:01:11.059 --> 00:01:12.220
I was searching for.
[AI] 我在找。

24
00:01:13.117 --> 00:01:14.808
Many years later.
[AI] 许多年后。

25
00:01:14.832 --> 00:01:17.548
I couldn't bear the thought of my son turning 13
[AI] 我无法忍受儿子13岁的想法

26
00:01:17.572 --> 00:01:20.357
without some kind of rite of passage.
[AI] 没有某种成年礼。

27
00:01:21.151 --> 00:01:24.635
So I came up with the idea of a 13th birthday trip.
[AI] 所以我想出了一个13岁生日旅行的主意。

28
00:01:24.659 --> 00:01:27.167
and I offered to take Murphy anywhere in the world
[AI] 我愿意带墨菲去世界上任何地方

29
00:01:27.191 --> 00:01:28.549
that had meaning for him.
[AI] 这对他有意义。

30
00:01:29.417 --> 00:01:32.116
A budding young naturalist who loved turtles.
[AI] 喜欢海龟的初露头角的年轻博物学家。

31
00:01:32.140 --> 00:01:34.256
he immediately settled on the Galapagos.
[AI] 他立即在加拉帕戈斯群岛定居下来。

32
00:01:35.133 --> 00:01:37.853
And when my daughter. Katie. turned 13.
[AI] 当我的女儿。凯蒂。13岁了。

33
00:01:37.877 --> 00:01:41.216
she and I spent two weeks at the bottom of the Grand Canyon.
[AI] 我和她在大峡谷的底部呆了两个星期。

34
00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:45.811
where Katie learned for the first time that she was powerful and brave.
[AI] 在那里，凯蒂第一次认识到她是强大和勇敢的。

35
00:01:46.610 --> 00:01:50.413
Since then. my partner. Ashton. and lots of our friends and relatives
[AI] 从那时起我的搭档。阿什顿。还有很多我们的朋友和亲戚

36
00:01:50.437 --> 00:01:53.405
have taken their kids on 13th birthday trips.
[AI] 带着孩子去参加13岁生日的旅行。

37
00:01:53.429 --> 00:01:58.426
with everyone finding it transformative for both the child and the parent.
[AI] 每个人都发现这对孩子和父母都有改变。

38
00:02:00.752 --> 00:02:02.618
I wasn't brought up saying grace.
[AI] 我从小就不是说格雷斯的。

39
00:02:03.529 --> 00:02:05.132
But for the last 20 years.
[AI] 但是在过去的20年里。

40
00:02:05.737 --> 00:02:08.093
we've been holding hands before every meal.
[AI] 我们每顿饭前都手牵手。

41
00:02:09.020 --> 00:02:11.114
It's a beautiful bit of shared silence
[AI] 这是一段美好的沉默

42
00:02:11.138 --> 00:02:13.429
that brings us all together in the moment.
[AI] 这让我们在这一刻走到了一起。

43
00:02:14.110 --> 00:02:17.041
Ashton tells everyone to "pass the squeeze."
[AI] 阿什顿告诉每个人“不要挤。”

44
00:02:17.065 --> 00:02:19.455
while she assures them it's not religious.
[AI] 虽然她向他们保证这不是宗教。

45
00:02:19.479 --> 00:02:20.943
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

46
00:02:22.261 --> 00:02:24.442
So recently. when my family asked me
[AI] 所以最近。当我的家人问我

47
00:02:24.466 --> 00:02:29.940
if I could please do something with the more than 250 boxes of stuff
[AI] 如果我能用超过250箱的东西做点什么的话

48
00:02:29.964 --> 00:02:31.997
that I've collected over a lifetime.
[AI] 这是我一生收集的。

49
00:02:32.639 --> 00:02:35.039
my ritual-making impulse kicked in.
[AI] 我的仪式制造冲动开始了。

50
00:02:36.387 --> 00:02:39.971
I started wondering if I could go further than simple death cleaning.
[AI] 我开始怀疑我是否能比简单的死亡清理更进一步。

51
00:02:40.807 --> 00:02:44.494
"Death cleaning" is the Swedish term for clearing out your closets.
[AI] “死亡清理”是瑞典语中用来清理你衣橱的术语。

52
00:02:44.518 --> 00:02:48.114
your basement and your attic before you die.
[AI] 在你死之前，你的地下室和阁楼。

53
00:02:48.138 --> 00:02:50.267
so your kids don't have to do it later.
[AI] 这样你的孩子以后就不用再做了。

54
00:02:50.291 --> 00:02:52.218
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

55
00:02:52.242 --> 00:02:55.645
I pictured my children opening up box after box
[AI] 我想象着我的孩子们打开一个又一个盒子

56
00:02:55.669 --> 00:02:59.139
and wondering why I'd kept any of that stuff.
[AI] 想知道我为什么要保留这些东西。

57
00:02:59.163 --> 00:03:00.368
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

58
00:03:00.392 --> 00:03:03.800
And then I imagined them looking at a specific picture
[AI] 然后我想象他们在看一张特定的照片

59
00:03:03.824 --> 00:03:06.315
of me with a beautiful young woman.
[AI] 我和一个漂亮的年轻女人在一起。

60
00:03:06.339 --> 00:03:09.372
and asking. "Who on earth is that with Dad?"
[AI] 问。“跟爸爸在一起的到底是谁？”

61
00:03:09.396 --> 00:03:10.792
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

62
00:03:10.816 --> 00:03:12.844
And that was the aha moment.
[AI] 这就是啊哈的时刻。

63
00:03:13.344 --> 00:03:16.419
It wasn't the things I'd saved that were important;
[AI] 重要的不是我保存的东西；

64
00:03:16.443 --> 00:03:19.993
it was the stories that went with them that gave them meaning.
[AI] 正是伴随着他们的故事赋予了他们意义。

65
00:03:21.374 --> 00:03:24.336
Could using the objects to tell the stories
[AI] 你能用这些东西讲故事吗

66
00:03:24.360 --> 00:03:26.033
be the seed of a new ritual.
[AI] 成为新仪式的种子。

67
00:03:26.660 --> 00:03:30.113
a rite of passage -- not for a 13-year-old.
[AI] 一个成人仪式——不适合13岁的孩子。

68
00:03:30.137 --> 00:03:32.476
but for someone much further down the road?
[AI] 但是对于一个更遥远的人来说？

69
00:03:34.288 --> 00:03:35.818
So I started experimenting.
[AI] 所以我开始做实验。

70
00:03:36.503 --> 00:03:39.139
I got a few dozen things out of the boxes.
[AI] 我从箱子里拿了几十件东西。

71
00:03:39.163 --> 00:03:40.784
I put them about in a room.
[AI] 我把它们放在一个房间里。

72
00:03:41.514 --> 00:03:43.381
and I invited people to come in
[AI] 我邀请人们进来

73
00:03:43.993 --> 00:03:46.812
and ask me about anything that they found interesting.
[AI] 问我他们觉得有趣的事。

74
00:03:48.317 --> 00:03:49.705
The results were terrific.
[AI] 结果非常好。

75
00:03:50.148 --> 00:03:55.198
A good story became a launching pad for a much deeper discussion.
[AI] 一个好故事成为一个更深入讨论的出发点。

76
00:03:55.222 --> 00:03:57.654
in which my visitors made meaningful connections
[AI] 我的访客在其中建立了有意义的联系

77
00:03:57.678 --> 00:03:58.902
to their own lives.
[AI] 为了他们自己的生活。

78
00:04:00.769 --> 00:04:04.163
Derrius [Quarles] asked me about a Leonard Peltier T-shirt
[AI] 德里奥斯[夸尔斯]问我一件莱纳德·佩尔蒂埃的T恤

79
00:04:04.187 --> 00:04:06.221
that I'd worn a lot in the '80s.
[AI] 我在80年代穿了很多。

80
00:04:06.245 --> 00:04:09.244
that. sadly. is still relevant today.
[AI] 那个悲哀地今天仍然相关。

81
00:04:09.744 --> 00:04:11.533
Our conversation moved quickly.
[AI] 我们的谈话进行得很快。

82
00:04:12.517 --> 00:04:16.300
from a large number of political prisoners in American jails.
[AI] 从美国监狱里的大量政治犯那里。

83
00:04:16.324 --> 00:04:18.536
to Derrius wondering about the legacy
[AI] 去德里奥斯想知道遗产

84
00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:21.490
of the Black Liberation Movement of the '60s.
[AI] 60年代的黑人解放运动。

85
00:04:21.514 --> 00:04:24.968
and how his life might be different if he'd come of age then.
[AI] 如果他长大了，他的生活会有什么不同。

86
00:04:24.992 --> 00:04:26.912
instead of 30-odd years later.
[AI] 而不是30多年后。

87
00:04:27.961 --> 00:04:29.570
At the end of our conversation.
[AI] 在我们谈话的最后。

88
00:04:30.285 --> 00:04:32.599
Derrius asked me if he could have the T-shirt.
[AI] 德里奥斯问我他能不能要这件T恤。

89
00:04:33.208 --> 00:04:36.106
And giving it to him felt just about perfect.
[AI] 给他感觉非常完美。

90
00:04:37.330 --> 00:04:40.663
As these conversations established common ground.
[AI] 因为这些对话建立了共同点。

91
00:04:40.687 --> 00:04:42.587
especially across generations.
[AI] 特别是跨越几代人。

92
00:04:43.468 --> 00:04:45.730
I realized I was opening a space
[AI] 我意识到我在打开一个空间

93
00:04:45.754 --> 00:04:48.742
for people to talk about things that really mattered to them.
[AI] 让人们谈论对他们来说真正重要的事情。

94
00:04:50.089 --> 00:04:53.571
And I started seeing myself with a renewed sense of purpose --
[AI] 我开始以一种新的使命感看待自己--

95
00:04:54.239 --> 00:04:56.132
not as the old guy on the way out.
[AI] 不像那个出去的老家伙。

96
00:04:56.756 --> 00:04:58.470
but as someone with a role to play
[AI] 但是作为一个可以扮演角色的人

97
00:04:58.494 --> 00:04:59.644
going forward.
[AI] 向前

98
00:05:01.590 --> 00:05:03.044
When I was growing up.
[AI] 当我长大的时候。

99
00:05:03.068 --> 00:05:05.600
life ended for most people in their 70s.
[AI] 大多数人的生命在70多岁时结束了。

100
00:05:07.355 --> 00:05:09.179
People are living far longer now.
[AI] 人们现在活得更长了。

101
00:05:09.884 --> 00:05:12.031
and for the first time in human history.
[AI] 这是人类历史上第一次。

102
00:05:12.055 --> 00:05:15.819
it's common for four generations to be living side by side.
[AI] 四代人并肩生活是很常见的。

103
00:05:16.891 --> 00:05:18.074
I'm 71.
[AI] 我71岁了。

104
00:05:18.717 --> 00:05:20.034
and with a bit of luck.
[AI] 还有一点运气。

105
00:05:20.058 --> 00:05:22.459
I've got 20 or 30 more years ahead of me.
[AI] 我还有二三十年的时间。

106
00:05:24.581 --> 00:05:26.247
Giving away my stuff now
[AI] 现在就把我的东西送人

107
00:05:26.851 --> 00:05:31.301
and sharing it with friends. family. and I hope strangers. too.
[AI] 并与朋友分享。家庭我希望是陌生人。也

108
00:05:31.887 --> 00:05:35.329
seems like the perfect way to enter this next stage of my life.
[AI] 似乎是进入我人生下一阶段的完美方式。

109
00:05:36.524 --> 00:05:38.609
Turns out to be just what I was looking for:
[AI] 结果证明这正是我想要的：

110
00:05:39.244 --> 00:05:41.679
a ritual that's less about dying
[AI] 与死亡无关的仪式

111
00:05:41.703 --> 00:05:43.646
and more about opening the door
[AI] 还有更多关于开门的事

112
00:05:43.670 --> 00:05:45.073
to whatever comes next.
[AI] 无论接下来发生什么。

113
00:05:45.965 --> 00:05:47.115
Thank you.
[AI] 非常感谢。

114
00:05:47.139 --> 00:05:48.229
(Applause)
[AI] （掌声）

115
00:05:48.253 --> 00:05:49.427
Onward!
[AI] 向前的！

116
00:05:49.451 --> 00:05:51.645
(Applause)
[AI] （掌声）